verses.text_plain: O come, let us sing unto the Lord: let us make a joyful noise to the rock of our salvation.
verses.verse_html: 1O come, let us sing unto the Lord: let us make a joyful noise to the rock of our salvation.

tokens.text: let us make a joyful noise

verses.text_plain: Let us come before his presence with thanksgiving, and make a joyful noise unto him with psalms.
verses.verse_html:
2Let us come before his presence with thanksgiving, and make a joyful noise unto him with psalms. ▼
▼ come…: Heb. prevent his face

footnotes.body_html: ▼ come…: Heb. prevent his face

verses.text_plain: For the Lord is a great God, and a great King above all gods.
verses.verse_html: 3For the Lord is a great God, and a great King above all gods.

verses.text_plain: In his hand are the deep places of the earth: the strength of the hills is his also.
verses.verse_html:
4In his hand are the deep places of the earth: the strength of the hills is his also. ▼
▼ In…: Heb. In whose
 , ▼
▼ the strength…: or, the heights of the hills are his

footnotes.body_html: ▼ In…: Heb. In whose

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the strength…: or, the heights of the hills are his
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the strength…: or, the heights of the hills are his

verses.text_plain: The sea is his, and he made it: and his hands formed the dry land.
verses.verse_html:
5The sea is his, and he made it: and his hands formed the dry land. ▼
▼ The sea…: Heb. Whose the sea is

footnotes.body_text: ▼ The sea…: Heb. Whose the sea is
footnotes.body_html: ▼ The sea…: Heb. Whose the sea is

verses.text_plain: O come, let us worship and bow down: let us kneel before the Lord our maker.
verses.verse_html: 6O come, let us worship and bow down: let us kneel before the Lord our maker.

verses.text_plain: For he is our God; and we are the people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand. To day if ye will hear his voice,
verses.verse_html: 7For he is our God; and we are the people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand. To day if ye will hear his voice,

verses.text_plain: Harden not your heart, as in the provocation, and as in the day of temptation in the wilderness:
verses.verse_html:
8Harden not your heart, as in the provocation, and as in the day of temptation in the wilderness: ▼
▼ provocation: Heb. contention

verses.text_plain: When your fathers tempted me, proved me, and saw my work.
verses.verse_html: 9When your fathers tempted me, proved me, and saw my work.

verses.text_plain: Forty years long was I grieved with this generation, and said, It is a people that do err in their heart, and they have not known my ways:
verses.verse_html: 10Forty years long was I grieved with this generation, and said, It is a people that do err in their heart, and they have not known my ways:

verses.text_plain: Unto whom I sware in my wrath that they should not enter into my rest.
verses.verse_html:
11Unto whom I sware in my wrath that they should not enter into my rest. ▼
▼ that…: Heb. if they enter into my rest

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that…: Heb. if they enter into my rest
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that…: Heb. if they enter into my rest
